To make kgerator start when the Raspberry Pi boots:

Add w1-gpio and w1-therm to /etc/modules
In /etc/inittab, change the tty0 login line that was
1:2345:respawn:/sbin/getty 38400 tty1
to be
1:23:respawn:/sbin/getty -i -a root -l /home/pi/kgerator-install/kgerator -o"" 38400 tty1

mkdir /home/pi/kgerator-install
cp kgerator /home/pi/kgerator-install/kgerator-vX
ln -s /home/pi/kgerator-install/kgerator-vX /home/pi/kgerator-install/kgerator


